  description: "Every corner of \\Place{Faer\\hat{u}n} harbors its own sinister element. When opportunities arise, malevolent groups and nefarious individuals emerge from the shadows to make their infamous marks on the \\Place{Realms}. Within these pages, you will discover everything players and Dungeon Masters need to create the most evil organizations, treacherous villains, and morally ambiguous antiheroes to ever afflict the \\Place{Forgotten Realms} game setting. \\list {3 new races} {Over 30 new spells} {New feats and prestige classes} Everything you need to know to play evil or morally ambiguous characters in the \\Place{Forgotten Realms} setting. \\Product{Champions of Ruin} is a comprehensive guide to playing evil characters in the \\Place{Forgotten Realms} setting. Many aspects of play are covered: vengeance, ambition, evil vs. evil, corruption and moral failure, loyalty and betrayal. The book also discusses types of evil -- lawful, chaotic, and neutral -- as well as morally ambivalent characters such as anti-heroes and rogues. Elder evils of extreme power are discussed along with tools, feats, spells, evil places and planar touchstones, and guilds and organizations that evil characters can join. Two new races are also introduced."
